WEBVTT

00:03.524 --> 00:05.427
I can give you many examples of that. Venezuelan 
equine encephalomyelitis

00:07.790 --> 00:14.380
entered the state of Texas in July of 1971. We had no 
expertise in that disease. I see. Whole cholera

00:20.568 --> 00:25.696
entered Texas in that same year from Mexico. Whole 
cholera is now a foreign animal disease. Exotic

00:30.237 --> 00:35.304
Newcastle disease has been diagnosed in Texas in 
poultry.

00:38.848 --> 00:39.509
Screw worms. Some of these diseases are not 
necessarily tropical diseases, but diseases

00:42.032 --> 00:56.751
that are foreign to this country and diseases in 
which a tremendous expertise should be developed

00:42.032 --> 00:56.751
in order to cope with them Before they hit, not 
after. We were caught with our pants down when VWE

00:59.412 --> 01:03.921
hit Texas. Which is what, VWE? Venezuelan equine 
cephalomyelitis. And if it hadn't been for the

01:09.391 --> 01:17.727
vaccine that had been developed by the Army at Fort 
Detrick, we would have been up the proverbial

01:09.391 --> 01:17.727
creek.

01:20.474 --> 01:31.187
So, in your opinion then, would you say, and I don't 
want to put words in your mouth, but would you say

01:20.474 --> 01:31.187
that this college and their research seems to be 
short-sighted? Well, Dr. Anderson, I think the

01:33.089 --> 01:50.110
reason- Or just too narrow and- No, the reason why 
the research isn't broader than it is is I think

01:51.743 --> 02:03.443
because all

01:51.743 --> 02:03.443
animal disease research now, practically all 
animal disease research is controlled through

01:51.743 --> 02:03.443
the Experiment Station. I think it should be the 
responsibility of the College of Veterinary

02:03.463 --> 02:11.878
Medicine to do animal disease research.

02:14.542 --> 02:22.291
The expertise for animal disease research 
resides in the College of Animal Medicine, not in

02:14.542 --> 02:22.291
the Experiment Station.

02:25.275 --> 02:40.093
And the

02:25.275 --> 02:40.093
present setup, whereby the director of the 
Experiment Station controlled the monies to fund

02:25.275 --> 02:40.093
animal disease research, I don't think is 
advantageous for the College of Veterinary

02:40.900 --> 02:45.606
Medicine. This is a political, infrastructural 
policy over which I exercise absolutely no say.

02:58.904 --> 03:10.620
But in my opinion, the College of Veterinary 
Medicine should be the sole agent for the

02:58.904 --> 03:10.620
university system in matters pertaining to 
animal disease research. This is not to say that

03:12.372 --> 03:23.985
some research should not be done collaboratively 
with the departments of animal science,

03:12.372 --> 03:23.985
entomology, or any other department. For 
example, in fish culture, mariculture study, we

03:25.808 --> 03:37.401
ought to cooperate with other departments on this 
campus in... in bringing the best minds of the

03:37.972 --> 03:43.962
university system to bear upon a problem. That's 
my opinion. In other words, it seems that we need

03:45.485 --> 03:50.994
more cooperation and coordination of our 
research efforts? I think that one of the things

03:51.455 --> 04:02.393
that is necessary is that the College of 
Veterinary Medicine be given

03:51.455 --> 04:02.393
more autonomy.

04:05.107 --> 04:16.043
There is no reason in the world why a research 
project that is written by a veterinary

04:05.107 --> 04:16.043
researcher ought to be approved by the experiment 
station. I think that's absurd. It should be

04:18.746 --> 04:23.133
approved by the dean here and then by the president 
of the university.

04:25.696 --> 04:33.848
I don't see any reason why we should respond to an 
intermediate agency that has no expertise in

04:34.840 --> 04:39.606
animal health, except the director. And the 
director is a veterinarian who had never

04:39.626 --> 04:45.494
functioned as a veterinarian for the last 20 years 
of his life. He's been an administrator.

04:51.662 --> 04:58.091
But you see, he used to be associate dean for 
research here before his promotion. But in my

04:58.111 --> 05:03.278
opinion, there isn't the fluidity of 
administrative matters

05:05.232 --> 05:31.070
that should circulate between this college and 
the Office of International Programs, for

05:05.232 --> 05:31.070
example, I think there should be more intimate 
contact between the Office of International

05:05.232 --> 05:31.070
Programs and the College of Veterinary Medicine 
in matters pertaining to animal health. I'm not

05:32.192 --> 05:33.113
talking about academic matters. I'm not talking 
about the possible recruitment of foreign

05:36.425 --> 05:44.576
students to the College of Veterinary Medicine. 
That's not what I'm talking about. I'm talking

05:46.579 --> 06:01.800
about capitalizing on opportunities that exist 
abroad for the research of animal diseases that

05:46.579 --> 06:01.800
could possibly threaten the welfare of this state 
and of this country. Let me give you an example.

06:08.221 --> 06:13.968
African swine fever is a deadly disease of swine 
for which there is no vaccine. Traditionally,

06:15.910 --> 06:26.884
African swine fever has been limited to Africa and 
to Spain and Portugal and other countries in that

06:15.910 --> 06:26.884
area of the world. But in 1978, this disease broke 
out in Brazil. From Brazil, it has spread to

06:32.965 --> 06:38.631
Dominican Republic, it has spread to Haiti, and 
it's now in Cuba. And it is too close for comfort. If

06:42.555 --> 06:48.242
it hits the United States, and I am convinced that 
it will enter the United States. I don't know when,

06:49.483 --> 06:53.647
but I think it will hit this country. And I think 
that this College of Veterinary Medicine ought to

06:54.088 --> 07:01.656
be readying for the time when this disease is going 
to hit our shores. And right now, there has been,

07:07.392 --> 07:16.141
for the last few years, a limitation of funds from 
the federal government for animal disease

07:07.392 --> 07:16.141
research. But what little monies there have come 
to the university, they have gone to the

07:17.122 --> 07:23.007
experiment station. Of course, the director of 
the experiment station has complete latitude to

07:23.027 --> 07:31.896
determine where that money should go. What agency 
in the country would be working on this African?

07:38.052 --> 08:01.579
Well, right now, for example, to answer your 
question, the United States Department of

07:38.052 --> 08:01.579
Agriculture is cooperating with the Food and 
Agricultural Organization of the United Nations

07:38.052 --> 08:01.579
to fund a team of people

07:38.052 --> 08:01.579
that is established in Santo Domingo, the 
Dominican Republic, to transfer the technology

08:03.449 --> 08:17.490
necessary for those people who diagnose African 
Swine Fever, and not only them, but also all the

08:03.449 --> 08:17.490
Caribbean countries and South and Central 
American countries. This university possesses

08:18.331 --> 08:27.685
the personnel that are qualified to head up that 
program, and I think international programs

08:29.302 --> 08:43.357
could very easily be the focal point from which a 
proposal could be turned into FAO and say, let

08:29.302 --> 08:43.357
Texas A&M provide the personnel and here's how 
much it would cost. They're looking for personnel

08:43.377 --> 08:56.912
right now, but it is, I think, there's been a 
discouragement of participation in in the

08:57.601 --> 09:02.247
international animal health problem.

09:02.267 --> 09:03.929
And here in our administration? In our own 
college, in our own university. Why do you think

09:08.034 --> 09:08.875
that is? Well, maybe because of the well-tried

09:09.756 --> 09:22.812
Texas axiom, you know, that what happens in other 
countries is no business of ours. We've got enough

09:23.613 --> 09:26.376
animal health problems in our own state we should 
direct our efforts to the solution of those and to

09:27.031 --> 09:31.858
hell with everybody else. I think that's the 
reason. Although I doubt very much that you would

09:34.261 --> 09:39.928
find anybody on this campus that would admit to 
that. That's the result.

09:44.094 --> 09:56.751
Also, if you disagree with existing policy and you 
try and point to people and say, We have to develop

09:57.743 --> 10:00.608
some knowledge about this disease. We can do it on 
foreign soil where it will not be a threat to Texas.

10:08.101 --> 10:17.937
We can make a significant contribution in this 
area by developing a vaccine against African

10:08.101 --> 10:17.937
swine fever or against babesiosis or against 
anaplasmosis. We have the opportunity to

10:18.959 --> 10:22.485
dispatch our people to foreign soil and let them 
set up a laboratory that that will work and address

10:23.461 --> 10:53.468
these problems without endangering our own uh 
situation at home and won't cost the state of Texas

10:23.461 --> 10:53.468
anything but you try and get these people to to uh to 
encourage that that type of thinking and they look

10:23.461 --> 10:53.468
the other way and they're the ones that are in 
charge of these decisions i've been very very

